<br>
The problem is, for a great while, the only people who will see emporer loots are people who have been doing the EQ thing for a few years. If you dont have a comparable cloak by now Im fairly comfortable saying that you will not see Emporer loot for a long while.<br>
<br>
After what is required to kill the emporer (bane camp for every melee, key camp for ever player, door keys for guild) the loot should outclass every other loot in the game. Right now its a disappointing upgrade. My guess is that they will upgrade a lot of Luclin loot. Remember when you first saw Vulak loot? ToV hosted the most difficult encounters for a long time. There were lots of wipes and lots of strats to learn. The payoff was a huge increase in guild power coming from quality loots. There is no Vulak/HoT quest item that isnt the best for its slot. The emporer encounter is MUCH more difficult than ToV ever was and requires MUCH, MUCH more time. The payoff should be shockingly nice loot. Huge focus bonuses, 125 hp/mana items, clickables with insane effects.<br>
<br>
What has happened is VI backed themselves into a corner lootwise. They dont know how to make things more uber without overpowering people. They learned their lesson with Trak CH bps. They dont want to make that same mistake again. Their first response to this was skill mod items. Their 2nd was focus items. The skill mod thing has yet to be tapped. There are no items out there with signifigant skill mod bumps except rogue backstab things. (And the Mrylo dagger/Ssra dagger skill mods already put them at 252 skill). They botched the focus thing by giving amazing power to mages the first day. Unfortunately, they have yet to implement the focus thing onto any droppable items. This will happen soon, as they are running out of things to put 100hp/mana on.<br>
<br>
They have the tools to make uber loot within their system now, they just have yet to implement it. This is why Im expecting a grand scale Luclin loot upgrade very soon. The items that are out there right now basically dont stand up to vulak loots. They know its bad, we know its bad.<br>
<br>
Sorry to rant way off topic, its just something thats been bothering me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  My point is that if this item is uber to you, you need to spend more time in EQ. EQ follows a linear progression when it comes to power increases. Once luclin landed it flatlined. They need to use the tools they created to make luclin items 'uber.' When you kill the emporer of ssra after all the horrible camps involved your first reaction to the loot should be &quot;WOW&quot; no matter where you are in Everquest.<br>
